cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.DS

The paper is about network embedding, which is a subfield of machine learning and data mining. The paper focuses on capturing both local and global structural information of a network, which is related to network analysis and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also proposes a novel algorithm for learning network embeddings, which is related to machine learning and deep learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also evaluates the proposed method on benchmark datasets, which is related to experimental evaluation and performance analysis. Therefore, cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper deals with network data, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
